B z ) was nearly unchanged for both Pi2s. This suggests that Polar was at or near a localized FLR excited by the oscillations of the fast mode waves. During the in situ FLR observation, Polar's footpoint was closest to the ground stations which recorded the amplitude maximum and the phase reversal in the H component.},
   author = {A Keiling and J R Wygant and C Cattell and K -H. Kim and C T Russell and D K Milling and M Temerin and F S Mozer and C A Kletzing},
